reviewContent: The watch looks very chic. Very cool, high quality, bright OLED display. Tested in all modes for a week. The battery holds very well, even unexpectedly better than it was on Samsung. Of the minuses: there is no Biesel, which is not convenient at first, there is no way to wind up an open workout or a timer, this is mega strange like for a smart watch. That is, you cannot start a timer, for example, go to the main screen or open a new workout in parallel. There is no sound signal when notified from applications, only vibration, although in the settings it is possible to enable this function, apparently the firmware bug. This function does not work with the iPhone. The sensors work very clearly, the sleep reads accurately, but does not correctly count the sleep time. For example: I fell asleep in the 1:30, woke up at 7.30, and the sleep time shows 7 hours. Apparently also a firmware bug. There is also a slight freeze with updated indicators. But I hope these all bugs will be corrected in the updates.

reviewContent:
Ugreen always impresses me with their quality, and they are my favorite brand. I often buy their products and have always been satisfied with the quality. I was really looking forward to these earbuds. The sound quality and material quality are excellent! I also really liked the fact that there’s an app to adjust and customize the earbuds.

However, there’s one huge downside that overshadows all the pros – these earbuds don’t fit in the ears at all. They just won’t stay in place, no matter how I try to adjust them. As far as I understand, they have a feature where the video or sound pauses when you take them out of your ear – but it doesn’t work properly. Even the slightest movement causes the video to stop, and I’m not even moving, just sitting still.

In short, it’s a big disappointment! I was really excited about these, but I wouldn’t recommend this model to anyone.
